Banco Finandina to Sell Up to 80 Billion Pesos of Debt Aug. 25

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-08-23T19:58:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/banco-finandina-to-sell-up-to-80-billion-pesos-of-debt-aug-25.html
Banco Finandina SA, a Colombian
lender, will offer as much as 80 billion pesos ($45 million) of
bonds in the local market Aug. 25.  The Bogota-based bank will offer 60 billion pesos of the
securities and make an additional 20 billion pesos available if
there is sufficient demand, brokerage Interbolsa SA, which is
helping manage the sale, said in a  report  today.  Banco Finandina will auction 24- and 36-month securities to
yield as much as 2.1 and 2.5 percentage points above the IBR
interbank rate, according to the report. The lender will also
offer 60-month debt to yield 4.4 percentage points above
inflation, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  